                  FROM user    WHERE id=?       user           SET ...          WHERE id=?

INPUTS NEEDED     nothing      ID from URL      JSON from      ID from URL      ID from URL
                                                body           + JSON from body


================================================================
        THE ONLY 4 THINGS THAT CHANGE BETWEEN METHODS
================================================================

    1. ANNOTATION
       @GetMapping / @PostMapping / @PutMapping / @DeleteMapping
       + whether it has ("/{id}") or not

    2. RETURN TYPE
       List<User>  → when returning multiple
       User        → when returning one
       String      → when nothing meaningful to return

    3. PARAMETERS
       nothing          → when request needs no input
       @PathVariable    → when ID comes from URL
       @RequestBody     → when data comes from body JSON
       both together    → PUT needs both

    4. JPA METHOD INSIDE
       findAll()        → get all rows
       findById()       → get one row
       save()           → insert or update
       deleteById()     → remove a row


================================================================
        WHAT STAYS THE SAME IN EVERY METHOD
================================================================

    → Always inside a class marked @RestController
    → Always public
    → Always uses the injected userRepository object
    → Always has a return statement (except void methods)
    → Spring always auto-converts return value to JSON
    → Method name never matters to Spring — only annotation matters
    → { } curly braces always wrap the method body


